                "text": "Here are the latest updates on London Underground services:\n\n- **General Service:** Most of the network is running smoothly. Always check the specific status of your line beforehand [TfL Service Status](https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/).\n  \n- **Northern Line:** There are partial closures planned between Hampstead and Edgware from December 13-14 for maintenance. Replacement buses will operate [Traffic Delays](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/).\n\n- **Christmas Period:** There will be no services on Christmas Day across all public transport, including the London Underground. However, services will resume with a reduced schedule on Boxing Day [TfL Christmas Travel](https://tfl.gov.uk/status-updates/major-works-and-events/christmas-and-new-year-travel).\n\n- **New Year's Eve:** Most services will run overnight to accommodate celebrations, but expect some station closures to manage crowds [TfL Christmas Travel](https://tfl.gov.uk/status-updates/major-works-and-events/christmas-and-new-year-travel).\n\nAlways consider using the TfL Go app or check the TfL website before traveling for real-time status updates.",
